ECB’s Orphanides Says Greek Default Would Be ’Catastrophic’

-- B y   M e e r a   L o u i s   a n d   M e e r a   L o u i s
-- 
2011-09-24T13:05:47Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-24/ecb-s-orphanides-says-greek-default-would-be-catastrophic-.html
European Central Bank Governing
Council member Athanasios Orphanides said “virtually all
central bankers and politicians agree” that a Greek default
would be “catastrophic.” He was speaking at a panel discussion
in  Washington  today.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Meera Louis in Washington at 
